[ProMED-mail thanks the contributors of this piece for pointing out
that yellow fever is more than a significant human health problem: it
poses risks to wild primate populations as well. As neotropical
forest primate habitat shrinks from human impacts, a fatal disease
such as yellow fever can further exacerbate pressures on already
declining primate populations. - Mod.TY]
